body:
Audit finding #16 — the `body` rule in dashboard/styles.css had been
doing two things at once:

  body {
      padding-top: env(safe-area-inset-top);
      padding-bottom: env(safe-area-inset-bottom);
      padding-left: env(safe-area-inset-left);
      padding-right: env(safe-area-inset-right);
      background-color: var(--color-base-100);
      color: var(--color-base-content);
  }

The safe-area padding is necessary (can't be expressed as a Tailwind
utility). The `background-color` / `color` pair was leftover from the
pre-DaisyUI custom-var era and is redundant under DaisyUI v5.

Verified via `cat node_modules/daisyui/base/rootcolor.css`:

    @layer base {
      :root, [data-theme] {
        background: var(--page-scroll-bg, var(--root-bg));
        color: var(--color-base-content);
      }
      :where(:root, [data-theme]) {
        --root-bg: var(--color-base-100);
      }
    }

DaisyUI paints the viewport background on the `html` element via
`[data-theme]` (the theme flash-prevention script sets data-theme on
<html>), which CSS treats as special — its background covers the
whole initial containing block. The cascade-root `color` is also set
on html, and body inherits it via the normal color cascade. Our
extra body background + color pair were overpainting with the
identical tokens DaisyUI already emitted.

Verified via grep of the built CSS bundle:

  $ grep 'body{' dist/assets/index-*.css
  }body{padding-top:env(...);padding-bottom:env(...);padding-left:env(...);padding-right:env(...)}

and

  $ grep ':root,\[data-theme\]' dist/assets/index-*.css
  }:root,[data-theme]{background:var(--page-scroll-bg,var(--root-bg));color:var(--color-base-content)}

Both rules ship; removing the body duplicate doesn't regress theme
rendering across any of the 8 themes.

This also clarifies the CLAUDE.md "element-selector exceptions"
documentation block: the body rule is now a single-concern
`env(safe-area-inset-*)` utility override, which matches the
comment's original scope. Before the cleanup, a reader seeing the
bg/color lines might reasonably wonder whether DaisyUI theming was
only half-wired. The file header comment was rewritten to document
the removal + the DaisyUI mechanism so a future session doesn't
re-add the redundant lines thinking they were missing.

Build clean (880.01 kB → 879.94 kB, -0.07 kB from the 2 removed
declarations), 60/60 tests pass. Visual verification across all 8
themes is captured as a TODO.md post-sweep-verification item.

